-- Gerresheimer Seeks to Double Sales Long-Term, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 2012-01-04T17:02:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/gerresheimer-seeks-to-double-sales-long-term-handelsblatt-says.html
Gerresheimer AG wants to double sales
to 2 billion euros long-term,  Handelsblatt  said, citing comments
by Chief Executive Officer Uwe Roehrhoff.  The company has a line of credit over 250 million euros
($323 million) and cash of 110 million euros that it can use for
acquisitions, and hopes to announce a transaction “soon,” the
newspaper said, citing the manager.  To contact the reporter on this story:
